channel.title: Custom models and some command errors?
channel.description:
First, I'm trying to add chaotic weapons to my server. I got the files, but they aren't the .gz or whatever. They're .dat files. They don't have the winrar icon next to them lol. Will they still work? Or does the winrar icon have to be next to them?
For the commands, I am trying to do ::corp to tele me to a corporal beast.
[code]if (command.equalsIgnoreCase("corp")){ teleportToX = 2265; teleportToY = 4699; }[/code]
I compiled and got no errors. But it doesn't tele me. Why?

item.title: Custom models and some command errors?
item.dc:creator: @Clawz_fury lare69
item.description:
@Clawz_fury wrote:

[quote=“adamknightz, post:4, topic:382291”][quote author=bender4 link=topic=478091.msg3498818#msg3498818 date=1297566625]
Okay, well looking at my Client.java I noticed that if (command.equalsIgnoreCase()){ is supposed to be if (command.startswith(“corp”)) { try changing it to that. If you were using else if, it would be else if (command.equalsIgnoreCase()){ so try what I said for the models, that should be in Client help not Server help
[/quote]

Models should not be under Client Help…they should be in the Model Requests/Help Section (http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/board,148.0.html).

And I’ve got the same question in Model Requests/Help and haven’t had an answer or any post for about 4 days or more (I think). So, good luck.[/quote]

If you have preloading you can use .dat files, but if you don’t you must GZIP them, and put them in your models folder.
You can GZIP Them by using a program by the name of: Gzip. Google it.

Question answered.
